description._content: TITLE Mount Monadnock, Cheshire County, NH CREATOR Keynart Co., Keene NH SUBJECT Mountains - NH Monadnock, Mount (N.H.) DESCRIPTION Postcard of Mount Monadnock, located in Cheshire County, New Hampshire, with Keene NH in the foreground, taken from Hyland Hill, which is west of Keene just over the town line of Westmoreland. Monadnock is said to be the second most climbed mountain in the world, after Mt. Fuji. It is 3,165 feet tall and stands alone above the surrounding landscape. The geological term "monadnock" is taken from this mountain and means an isolated, erosin-resistant mountain that rises abruptly from its surroundings.
